  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "The vending machine sold apples, bananas, cheese crackers, and small bottles of juice, along with the mysterious purple drink.",
      "zh": "那台自動販賣機賣蘋果、香蕉、起司餅乾，還有小瓶果汁，當然也有那款神秘的紫色飲料。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice bought a coffee and a bag of popcorn while they waited to start asking questions.",
      "zh": "他們準備開始問問題之前，Bernice 買了一杯咖啡和一包爆米花。"
    },
    {
      "en": "The new note came with a name signed at the bottom, which almost never happened.",
      "zh": "這張新紙條底下還簽了名字，這種事幾乎從來沒發生過。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It read: \"Ask me anything. I just want to know why my favorite drink never runs out.\"",
      "zh": "紙條上寫著：「你們可以問我任何問題，我只是想知道，為什麼我最喜歡的那款飲料永遠不會賣完。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Finally,\" Bernice said, \"a case where the person actually wants to be found.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 說：「終於，一個當事人自己想被找到的案子。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco smiled. \"Let me guess your first idea,\" she said. \"Another secret hero, quietly keeping it stocked just for one student.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 笑了：「我猜猜你的第一個想法，」她說：「又是一個默默補貨、只為了一個學生的秘密英雄。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice looked slightly caught. \"Maybe,\" she admitted.",
      "zh": "Bernice 看起來有點被說中了：「也許吧，」她承認。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Mr. Pan, who happened to hear them, looked over from his desk.",
      "zh": "剛好聽到他們對話的潘老師，從他的桌子那邊看了過來。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Two good cases don't make a rule,\" he said. \"Every case starts at zero.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「兩個好案子不代表就有規則，每個案子都要從零開始查。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "So they started with the simplest question: who fills the machine, and how often?",
      "zh": "所以他們從最簡單的問題開始：是誰在補貨，多久補一次？"
    },
    {
      "en": "The answer came from the school office again: a drink company visited every Monday and Thursday, refilling every machine the same way.",
      "zh": "答案又是從學校辦公室來的：一家飲料公司每星期一和星期四都會來，用一樣的方式補滿每一台機器。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"So nobody at school is secretly refilling it,\" Coco said, sounding a little upset.",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「所以沒有人在學校裡偷偷補貨。」她的語氣聽起來有點失落。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"That's not the real question anyway,\" Bernice said slowly. \"The real question is why it doesn't run out between Monday and Thursday.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 慢慢地說：「反正那也不是真正的問題，真正的問題是，為什麼它在星期一到星期四之間不會賣完。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Every other drink in that machine sold out fast. That one stayed almost full, day after day.",
      "zh": "那台機器裡的其他飲料都賣得很快，只有那一款，每天都幾乎是滿的。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Maybe it's broken,\" Coco said. \"Maybe it just looks full.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 說：「也許它壞了，也許只是看起來是滿的。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "They checked. It wasn't broken. Students really could buy it, any time they wanted.",
      "zh": "他們檢查過了，並沒有壞，學生真的隨時都可以買到。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Then people just aren't buying it,\" Bernice said. \"As simple as that.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 說：「那就是根本沒有人在買，就這麼簡單。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco wasn't sure \"simple\" was the right word yet. \"But why not?\" she asked. \"It's someone's favorite drink.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 還不確定「簡單」是不是正確的說法：「但為什麼不買？」她問：「這可是有人最喜歡的飲料。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice picked up her notebook and wrote down a short plan: ask ten students the same simple question.",
      "zh": "Bernice 拿起筆記本，寫下一個簡短的計畫：問十個學生同一個簡單問題。"
    },
    {
      "en": "They separated at lunch, one on each side of the cafeteria, ready to start asking.",
      "zh": "午餐時間他們分開行動，一個人負責餐廳的一邊，準備開始問問題。"
    }
  ],
